        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>rotated indexes [300026558], indexes by form [300026555], indexes (reference sources) [300026554], reference sources [300163404], documents by function [300137955], document genres [300026031], information forms (objects) [300220751], Information Forms (hierarchy name) [300026029], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Indexes in which each significant word in the entry is brought to the beginning, in alphabetical order, followed by the remaining words which follow it, and then followed by that part of the original title which came before the significant word.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000025071/Harrod's Librarians' Glossary (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Índices en los que cada palabra clave de la entrada se coloca al principio, en orden alfabético, seguida por las palabras restantes que vienen a continuación, y después seguida por esa parte del título original que venía antes de la palabra clave.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Indexen waarin ieder hoofdwoord in het artikel naar voren wordt gehaald, op alfabetische volgorde, gevolgd door de resterende woorden die erna komen, en daarna gevolgd door dat deel van de originele titel dat voor het hoofdwoord kwam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052431/Dictionary of library science (1973)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>索引條目中之每個，將重要關鍵字彙被置於提至開頭，並依字母順序排列，繼之後接著以其後的剩餘的字彙，最然後才則是該重要字彙的原始標題的內容。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
